Installation
============

1. Backup your .vimrc file and .vim directory

2. In your home, do:

	git clone git://github.com/txusty/vim-rails.config.git .vim
	
	ln -s .vim/vimrc .vimrc

        And if you like gvim:

	ln -s .vim/gvimrc .gvimrc

3. Enjoy!

Cheatsheet
==========

(<leader> is ',')

Custom Mappings
---------------

<leader> p - Toggle NERDtree project explorer
<leader> t - FuzzyFinderTextMate
<leader> b - Explore open buffers in FuzzyFinderTextMate
F5 - Reload FuzzyFinder tree
<leader> tl - Toggle Tag List
<Control> v - Paste from outside VIM
<Control> s - Save

VIM Grep
--------

:lvim /string_to_search/g **/*.extension
:lw - Rotate among results

Misc
---------
:(range)s/old/new/g - Search and replace
  Example: :%s/old/new/g
           :10,30s/old/new/g

